On 2003-10-09 at 19:04 +0100, Peter Stephenson wrote:
> Sure the %z shouldn't be %Z?  Solaris doesn't like %z.

%z is a common extension to strftime(), which gives the off-set
numerically.

Eg:

 %Z CEST
 %z +0200

The %z is not part of POSIX.
